bug.short_desc: Load runtime is very high in Chrome 45

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1384 Screenshot of load runtime for IE 11 vs Chrome 45
After the update to Chrome 45 the time to load a newly created qooxdoo application, served using "generate.py source-server", is very high (50s). The problem is not present in IE 11 which loads in <3s.

Hi, I doubt that's related to framework code. Might rather be an issue with your Crome installation or its integration into your OS. For instance, Win10 known to have Chrome issues. Or some plugins / antivirus / firewalling software?
Checked with Chrome 45 on Mac, and a qooxdoo 5.0 skeleton starts up in about 1sec, even the full source version.
